Notice of Non-Discrimination and Reservation of Rights

Palmer College of Chiropractic (College) does not discriminate in employment, admissions or in educational practices, programs, services or activities on the basis of age, ancestry, citizenship status, color, creed, disability, national origin, race, religion, sex, sexual orientation, gender identity, veteran status or other characteristic protected by law in the state in which the applicable College premise is located.

Palmer College of Chiropractic reserves the right, without notice, to modify its requirements for admission or graduation; to change the arrangements or content of its courses and the instructional materials used, or to alter any regulation affecting the student body; to refuse admission or readmission to any student at any time, or to dismiss any student at any time, should it be in the interest of the College, or of the student, to do so. The College also reserves the same right as to any other material in this publication.

This application may be denied admissions based on a number of factors including, but not limited to, past academic performance, past academic or ethics violations, criminal activity or dishonesty in the admissions process. If you wish to withdraw your application at anytime, contact your Admissions Representative for processing.

Applicants are promptly notified as documents are received and each step of the        application is completed. Only written communication directly from Undergraduate        Studies shall be considered official. Acceptance is based on the approval of the        completed file. Applicants will be notified of their current status. The balance of the        first academic term tuition is due on orientation day. If the applicant does not begin        Palmer in the academic term requested and Undergraduate Studies is unable to make        contact, the file will be destroyed. The prospective student must then reapply and        resubmit all necessary documents.

Join us in celebrating the chiropractic profession's 125th anniversary.
What do you see on the horizon? We see you at Palmer.
Save time and money by earning your B.S. and D.C. at Palmer.
It started with a movement of hands that changed spinal health and well-being forever.
Be a part of the celebration >

At Palmer College of Chiropractic, the first and largest chiropractic college, you can count on excellence in teaching and real-world preparation. You'll experience an academic program that blends theory with hands-on clinical skills designed to prepare you for success in your professional practice.
There is a vast difference between treating effects and adjusting the cause.
D.D. Palmer, Discoverer of Chiropractic and Founder of Palmer College of Chiropractic

At Palmer you’ll be trained and prepared – academically and professionally – for success in your future practice.
There’s no better time to apply than now.
Apply to B.S. Completion Program Now

We accept applications for our D.C. program at any time. However, we recommend you submit your application at least one (1) year prior to your desired term. That’s because your start date and financial aid eligibility may be affected by your application submission date.
Submit a one- to two-page typed
explaining why you’re choosing a career in chiropractic and why you want to get your Doctor of Chiropractic degree from Palmer College of Chiropractic.
Submit official transcripts where any college level courses were taken (send to the Davenport address above).
on official letterhead – one from a doctor of chiropractic and one from a college faculty member. (This is required for Florida-campus students and recommended for Davenport and West campuses.)
Although not required at time of application, applicants will be asked to submit a tuition deposit and complete their background check authorization and admissions interview prior to acceptance.
National Association letter of approval (if needed)
score or proof of English proficiency
Disclosure statement of any criminal convictions
While you wait for acceptance you may gain provisional acceptance by completing or submitting the following:
A completed transfer form (if you have attended another chiropractic college)
If you have withdrawn from Palmer and are applying for re-admission, requirements vary based on the length of your absence.
for further information regarding re-admission or see our course
You might be able to save a year's worth of time and tuition through one of our

. Our 3 1, 2 2 or duel enrollment programs offer accelerated, cost-effective way to meet prerequisite requirements for the Doctor of Chiropractic program. Save a year's worth of time and tuition by starting your college education at one of our partner schools. Programming is designed specifically for Palmer students.
Bachelor of Science in General Science – Main campus only

Applications for the Bachelor of Science in General Science program can be submitted and accepted at any time. However, we recommended you apply a minimum of three (3) months prior to your desired term because your start date and financial aid eligibility may be affected by your submission date.
(Note: Your admittance is approved by the Undergraduate Program Oversight Committee.)
Pay $100 graduation and records fee. Complete Intent to Graduate form for final approval of the B.S. degree.
We recommend the Intent to Graduate form be completed no later than the end of ninth trimester of the D.C. program. This will ensure concurrent graduation.
Note: Students are allowed one year after their D.C. graduation to complete all requirements.
